org.gearvrf.io

Class GVRInputManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.gearvrf.io.GVRInputManager

  • public abstract class GVRInputManager
extends java.lang.Object
    An instance of this class is obtained using the GVRContext.getInputManager() call. Use this class to query for all the GVRCursorController objects in the framework. Use the addCursorControllerListener(CursorControllerListener) call to notify the application whenever a GVRCursorController is added or removed from the framework. Alternatively use the getCursorControllers() method to know all the devices currently in the framework. The class also allows external input devices to be added using the addCursorController(GVRCursorController) method.

    • Method Detail

      • getCursorControllers

        public java.util.List<GVRCursorController> getCursorControllers()
        Get a list of the GVRCursorControllers currently in the system. Ideally this call needs to be done inside GVRMain.onInit(GVRContext) so that all the cursor objects are set up before the rendering starts. Remember to add a CursorControllerListener to receive notifications on GVRCursorController objects added or removed during runtime.
        Returns:
        a list of all the GVRCursorController objects in the system.

      • isConnectedToAndroidWearTouchpad

        public boolean isConnectedToAndroidWearTouchpad()
        Queries the status of the connection to the Android wear watch.
        Returns:
        true if android wear touchpad is connected, else false.
